    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-03T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.6363/24a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-03T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. With reference to your despatch No. 898 of October 22, 1926. Endeavor to
                    ascertain the views of your British and Rumanian colleagues on the question of
                    petroleum storage and the nature of any representations which they may have made
                    to the Egyptian Government. Also ascertain whether, if the protested practice
                    continues, they would be in favor of joint or concurrent representations and, in
                    such event, the nature of the arguments upon which they would be prepared to
                    base such action.</p>
                <p>Report the results of your conversations briefly by telegraph, also the present
                    status of the controversy and your recommendations. Report fully on the subject
                    by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
